# Transport-layer security headers for nomad.md
# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
# This file is consumed by Netlify, Cloudflare Pages, and any
# static host that supports the `_headers` format. GitHub Pages
# does NOT honour `_headers`; deploy the equivalent via `<meta
# http-equiv>` tags in `src/app.html` (we ship a `frame-ancestors`
# fallback there) and via the static-host-specific config (e.g.
# `_redirects` for SPA fallback, see `docs/hosting/github-pages.md`).
#
# Policy choices (v0 вЂ” sub-phase 6L, audit carry-over):
#  - `default-src 'self'` вЂ” strict default; only same-origin by
#    default. Every directive below is an explicit carve-out.
#  - `script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'` вЂ” v0 trade-off. The
#    no-flash theme bootstrap in `src/app.html` is a single inline
#    `<script>` that must run before first paint. `adapter-static`
#    does not support per-build nonces, and `strict-dynamic` would
#    require the same. `'unsafe-inline'` keeps the no-flash
#    contract while we evaluate the per-build nonce follow-up
#    (documented in `docs/audits/2026-06-23/step-6-csp.md`).
#  - `style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'` вЂ” Tailwind 4 + Svelte's
#    component-scoped styles occasionally emit inline `style="вЂ¦"`
#    attributes for transitions. Same trade-off; the per-build
#    nonce follow-up covers both directives together.
#  - `img-src 'self' data: blob:` вЂ” Markdown rendering and
#    inline image previews use `data:` URIs (favicons, embedded
#    SVGs) and `blob:` (DOMPurify image sinks).
#  - `connect-src 'self' https://cors.isomorphic-git.org
#     https://*.github.com https://*.gitlab.com` вЂ” Remote Mode's
#    CORS proxy plus the Git provider HTTP transport. The
#    wildcard host entries are non-negotiable per the audit:
#    `modeStore.openRemote()` POSTs to whatever the user typed,
#    which is always `*.github.com` or `*.gitlab.com` for the
#    supported providers. `self` is required for SvelteKit's
#    data fetching.
#  - `object-src 'none'` вЂ” defence-in-depth against `<object>` /
#    `<embed>` (Flash is dead, but the directive costs nothing).
#  - `base-uri 'none'` вЂ” no `<base>` injection. The brief's v0
#    template mandates `'none'`; this is a small strengthening
#    over the previous `'self'` and disables all `<base>` tags.
#  - `frame-ancestors 'none'` вЂ” clickjacking defence. The `<meta
#    http-equiv>` fallback in `src/app.html` covers the case
#    where the host strips headers.
#  - `form-action 'none'` вЂ” the app is a client-side SPA with
#    no `<form>` submissions; `'none'` is the strict v0 choice.
#    If a future form is added, change to `'self'`.
#  - `require-trusted-types-for 'script'` вЂ” opt the app into
#    Trusted Types; the renderer + DOMPurify policy is the
#    documented sink.
#  - `trusted-types nomad-md dompurify default` вЂ” the policy
#    name. Required for the `require-trusted-types-for`
#    directive to be useful (otherwise every DOM sink is denied
#    with no way to construct a TrustedHTML value).
#
# Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000 (2 years)
# includeSubDomains preload вЂ” the `preload` directive is only
# effective after submission to the HSTS preload list
# (hstspreload.org). Shipping it from day 1 documents the
# intent; sites that submit must remove the directive to
# reverse the commitment.
# X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff вЂ” prevents MIME-type sniffing.
# Referrer-Policy: no-referrer вЂ” the URL bar never leaks the
# current path.
# Permissions-Policy: every common sensor / API denied by
# default (camera, microphone, geolocation, interest-cohort,
# payment, USB, serial, Bluetooth, MIDI).
# Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin вЂ” process isolation.
# Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp вЂ” required for
# SharedArrayBuffer (the jsdom renderer test path relies on
# it) and isolates the page.
# Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin вЂ” refuse to be
# embedded as a subresource by cross-origin pages.

/
	Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
	X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
	Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
	Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), interest-cohort=(), payment=(), usb=(), serial=(), bluetooth=(), midi=()
	Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
	Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
	Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
	Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://cors.isomorphic-git.org https://*.github.com https://*.gitlab.com; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'none'; require-trusted-types-for 'script'; trusted-types nomad-md dompurify default

/_app/immutable/*
	Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
